The Nigeria Center for Disease and Control, NCDC, on Thursday confirmed 108 new cases of Coronavirus. NCDC, in a tweet on its official Twitter page, disclosed that the confirmed cases were as follows: 78 in Lagos, 14 in FCT, 5 in Ogun, 4 in Gombe, 3 in Borno, 2 in Akwa Ibom, 1 in Kwara, and 1 in Plateau. This brings the number of confirmed cases to a total of 981 in Nigeria. The tweet read: “108 new cases of #COVID19 have been reported; “As at 11:30pm 23rd April there are 981 confirmed cases of #COVID19 reported in Nigeria, 197 have been discharged with 31 deaths.”